Fixed the health check handlers across all services to accept both GET and HEAD requests. The issue was that Docker's healthcheck uses `wget --spider` which sends HEAD requests by default, but the health handlers only accepted GET requests (causing 405 errors).

**Changes made:**

| Service | File | Change |
|---------|------|--------|
| registry-service | `services/registry-service/main.go` | Accept HEAD for `/health` |
| job-service | `services/job-service/main.go` | Accept HEAD for `/health` |
| auth-service | `services/auth-service/main.go` | Accept HEAD for `/health` |
| notification-service | `services/notification-service/main.go` | Accept HEAD for `/health` |
| storage-service | `services/storage-service/main.go` | Accept HEAD for `/health` |

**Note:** The 401 Unauthorized errors for `/agents/heartbeat` are expected - these are from agents sending heartbeats without valid authentication tokens. This is normal security behavior.

After rebuilding and restarting the Docker containers, the 405 healthcheck errors should be resolved.
